    <item>
      <title>Resolving NGINX 502 Bad Gateway Errors After OS Upgrade</title>
      <link>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/resolve-nginx-502-bad-gateway-errors-os-upgrade/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 22 Jun 2026 08:23:51 &#43;0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/resolve-nginx-502-bad-gateway-errors-os-upgrade/</guid>
      <description>The NGINX 502 Bad Gateway error typically occurs when there&amp;rsquo;s an issue with the server acting as a gateway or proxy, often due to configuration problems or server overload. To resolve this error after an OS upgrade, review your server configuration and ensure that all services are properly restarted and configured.</description>
